ObjectStates.Name: ScriptingTrigger
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
function onLoad()
    -- recount()
end

function onObjectLeaveScriptingZone(zone, obj)
    recount()
end

function onObjectEnterScriptingZone(zone, obj)
    if zone!= self then
        return
    end
    if getAddedValue(obj) == nil then
        return
    end
    local sum = getTotal(zone) + getAddedValue(obj)
    setSum(sum)	
end

function getAddedValue(obj)
    local quantity = obj.getQuantity()	
    local unitary_value = obj.getVar('value')
    if unitary_value == nil then
        return nil
    end
    if quantity >= 0 then
        return unitary_value * quantity
    end
    return unitary_value
end

function onObjectDestroy(obj)
    if zone!= self then
        return
    end
    local sum = getTotal() - getAddedValue(obj)
    getObjectFromGUID('a1a0fd').setVar('sum', sum)
    updateCounter(sum)
end

function getTotal()
    local objs = self.getObjects()
    local sum = 0
    for k, v in pairs(objs) do
        local value = getAddedValue(v)
        if value != nil then
            sum = sum + value
        end
    end
    return sum
end

function updateCounter(number)
    getObjectFromGUID('5e652e').setValue(number)
end

function setSum(sum)
    self.setVar('sum', sum)
    updateCounter(sum)
end

function recount()
    local sum = getTotal()
    setSum(sum)
end

ObjectStates.LuaScript:
stackSize = 4*2

function onLoad()
    params = {
        click_function = "click_func",
        function_owner = self,
        label          = "Update Road",
        position       = {0, 0.2, 0},
        width          = 2800,
        height         = 900,
        font_size      = 340,
        color          = {0.5, 0.5, 0.5},
        font_color     = {1, 1, 1},
    }
    self.createButton(params)
end

function click_func(obj, color, alt_click)
    Global.call("onUpdateRoad")
end

LuaScript:
--[[ Lua code. See documentation: http://berserk-games.com/knowledgebase/scripting/ --]]

--[[ The onLoad event is called after the game save finishes loading. --]]
function onLoad()
    --[[ print('onLoad!') --]]
    updateSeated()	
end    

--[[ The onUpdate event is called once per frame. --]]
function onUpdate ()
    --[[ print('onUpdate loop!') --]]
end

function onPlayerChangeColor(color)
    updateSeated()
end

function onPlayerConnect(person)
    updateSeated()
end

function Set (list)
    local set = {}
    for _, l in ipairs(list) do set[l] = true end
    return set
end

players_no = 0
MIN_PLAYERS = 2
CARDS4P = Set{"13ce97", "3142e2", "3c5481", "e35cad", "0a0349", "13ce97", "518024", "23cb5a", "9e9431", "4382a7", "0b72a9", "ec7be9", "8f340c", "85d426"} 

function updateSeated()
    players_no = #getSeatedPlayers()
    UI.setAttribute("setup_button", "tooltip", 
"Currently " .. players_no .. " sitting (" .. MIN_PLAYERS .. " required)")
    if players_no >= MIN_PLAYERS then
        UI.setAttribute("setup_button", "interactable", true)
        UI.setAttribute("setup_button", "text", "Setup for " .. players_no .. " players")
    else
        UI.setAttribute("setup_button", "text", "More players required")
        UI.setAttribute("setup_button", "interactable", false)
    end
end

function shuffle_and_deal()
    mergeStackWithReserve()
    randomizeReserve()
    setStacks(players_no * 2)
    deal(5)
end

function deal()
    local reserve = getReserve()
    reserve.deal(5)
end

function onUpdateRoad()

    road = getRoadZone()
    
    for k, card in pairs(road.getObjects()) do
        
        if card.getName() != "1 gold" then
            pos = card.getPosition()
            zoneSpawn = {
                position = pos,
                scale = { 2.5, 1, 4 },
                type = 'ScriptingTrigger',
                callback_function = function(obj) zoneCallback(obj, card) end,
                rotation = card.getRotation(),
            }
            spawnObject(zoneSpawn)
        end
    end
end

function getRoadZone()
    return getObjectFromGUID('1b37f5')
end

function zoneCallback(zone, card)
    there_was_a_coin = false
    pos = card.getPosition()
    for _,o in ipairs(zone.getObjects()) do
        if card != o then
            there_was_a_coin = true
        end
    end

    zone.destruct() --destroy the zone when you're done with it, to avoid clutter.

    if not there_was_a_coin and players_no >=3 then
        -- Place coin
        pos.z = pos.z - 1
        getObjectFromGUID('c9d32c').takeObject({
            position = pos,
        })
    elseif (not there_was_a_coin and players_no < 3) or 
           (there_was_a_coin and players_no >= 3) then
        -- Discard and refresh
        discard(card)
        putFromReserve(pos)
    end
end

function discard(card)
    card.setPositionSmooth({19.5, 5, -2.6}, false, true)
end

function putFromReserve(pos)
    flipped = {0, 180, 0}
    getReserveDirectly().takeObject({position=pos, rotation=flipped})
end

function getReserveDirectly()
    local reserveID = 'd94bb6'
    return getObjectFromGUID(reserveID)
end

function setup_for_x_players(obj, color, alt_click)
    if players_no >= 4 then
        merge4pWithReserve()
    else
        set4pCardsAside()
    end
    mergeStackWithReserve()
    randomizeReserve()
    setStacks(players_no * 2)
end

function set4pCardsAside()
    local zone = getRandomZone()
    for _, deck in pairs(zone.getObjects()) do
        for _, card in pairs(deck.getObjects()) do
            if CARDS4P[card["guid"]] then
                deck.takeObject({
                    guid=card["guid"],
                    position={24, 1, -2.4}
                })
            end
        end
    end
end

function randomizeReserve()
    local res = getReserve()
    res.shuffle()
    --print(#(res.getObjects()))
    --getObjectFromGUID('30eba5').randomize()
end

function setStacks(amount)
    local reserve = getReserve()
    for i=0, 5 do
        stack = reserve.cut(amount)[2]
        stack.setRotation({0, 180, 180})
        stack.setPosition({-6 + 3*i, i+2, -1.2})
    end
end

function merge4pWithReserve()
    local deck4p = '410af7'
    local reserve = getReserve()
    local deck = getObjectFromGUID(deck4p)
    if deck!=nil then
        reserve.putObject(deck)
    end
end

function mergeStackWithReserve()
    local resPose = getReservePos()
    local reserve = getReserve()
    local randomZone = getRandomZone()
    for k,v in pairs(randomZone.getObjects()) do
        if v!=reserve then
            reserve.putObject(v)
        end
    end
end

function getRandomZone()
    return getObjectFromGUID('ec629e')
end

function getReservePos()
    local reserve = getReserve()
    return reserve.getPosition()
end

function getReserve()
    local reserveZoneID = '12db86'
    return getObjectFromGUID(reserveZoneID).getObjects()[1]
end
